## Run locally

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
streamlit run app.py
```

You can also use the script entry point:

```bash
dcca-dashboard
```

To export the generated analytics table:

```bash
python scripts/build_analytics_dataset.py
```

---

## Tests

```bash
pytest -q
```

Coverage in this version is focused on the parts that should be stable and defendable:
- transforms
- metrics
- filters
- chart factories

---

## Why this project is defensible in interview

Because it does not oversell the data.

It makes explicit technical tradeoffs:
- it uses the curated file as the main business layer
- it enriches from raw modules without pretending to perfectly reconstruct all raw semantics
- it favors interpretable feature engineering over decorative complexity
- it shows business-relevant outputs instead of generic survey plots
- it documents the integration limitation clearly

